SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 894
By Massey
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Knoxville Community
Media on the occasion of its fiftieth anniversary.
WHEREAS, this General Assembly takes great pleasure in recognizing a nonprofit
organization that has helped promote and preserve free speech in its community for the past
fifty years; and
WHEREAS, Knoxville Community Media (KCM) is an independently chartered 501(c)(3)
organization created in 1975 to serve the community of Knoxville and Knox County by providing
public, educational, and government access through television and other media outlets; and
WHEREAS, the existence of KCM encourages civic engagement and participation
through its coverage and archiving of gavel-to-gavel government meetings; and
WHEREAS, KCM assists educational entities, organizations, community groups, and
nonprofit organizations in sharing their mission with the community; and
WHEREAS, KCM offers life-skills training and equipment that enable the citizens of
Knoxville and Knox County to share their beliefs, dreams, and values through a media platform
for free speech; and
WHEREAS, KCM was a vital resource during the COVID-19 pandemic and has
continued to offer all of the aforementioned services at little or no cost to the community, even in
the face of revenue loss; and
WHEREAS, KCM remains a true beacon of unfiltered free thought, free expression, and
free speech, providing a modern form of the public town square in a media age in which many
media outlets do not allow unfiltered free thought, free expression, or free speech; and
WHEREAS, KCM and its staff are richly deserving of our approbation on this special
occasion; now, therefore,
SJR0894
014604
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and recognize Knoxville Community
Media upon fifty years of service to the community as a champion of free speech, as KCM looks
forward to fifty more years of responsible, thoughtful, and important media-making and the
preservation of localism in media.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
